Section 1:
1 L.D. 526
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 345, L.D. 526, “An Act to Reduce the
10 Time Period for Challenging the Validity of a Property Tax Lien on Commercial Real
11 Estate”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 5 in the 5th line (page 1, line 7 in L.D.) by
13 striking out the following: "used primarily for business purposes" and inserting the
14 following: 'either used or held for use primarily for a business purpose'
15 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
16 number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment clarifies that commercial real estate need not necessarily be in active
1199 business use to be included under the provisions of the bill.
Page 1 - 132LR1172(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
